<article class="list content widget expert-content" itemprop="articleBody">
		<section class="list-unit group">
			<div class="expert-content-text"><p>Beginning quilters are sometimes overwhelmed by the hundreds of new terms and techniques they encounter when they make their first quilt, and the confusion is often compounded because of the many ways to accomplish every quiltmaking task. You&#39;ll discover which quilting methods work best for you as you become more experienced, but getting comfortable with the must-know skills will help you sew <a href="/od/beginningquilters/a/easy_quilts.htm" data-inlink="nh2ogu-WPyITXby3I7EYIw&#61;&#61;" data-component="link" data-source="inlineLink" data-type="internalLink" data-ordinal="1">accurate quilts on your very first try</a>.</p></div>
		</section>


		<section class="list-unit group">
		<figure class="content-img content-img-small right-gutter">
			<div class="content-img-wrapper">
<img src="http://f.tqn.com/y/quilting/1/L/M/C/0/-/Vintage-Quilt-with-Sashing-edit.jpg" alt="Quilt - Marcie Cheatham / E+ / Getty Images" width="300" height="200" class="" data-pinit-img-url="http://f.tqn.com/y/quilting/1/S/M/C/0/-/Vintage-Quilt-with-Sashing-edit.jpg" data-description="10 Things Every Quilter Should Know About Quilting: Learn About Fabric" itemprop="image" >
			
<a href="http://pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=http://quilting.about.com/od/quiltpatternsprojects/tp/quilting_skills.htm?utm_source=pinterest&amp;utm_medium=social&amp;utm_campaign=shareurlbuttons_nip&media=http://f.tqn.com/y/quilting/1/S/M/C/0/-/Vintage-Quilt-with-Sashing-edit.jpg&description=10 Things Every Quilter Should Know About Quilting: Learn About Fabric" data-component="contentListPage" data-source="pinitBtn" data-type="sharePinterest" data-ordinal="1" data-network="pinterest" title="Pin to Pinterest" class="pinit-btn" data-pin-do="skipLink"></a>			</div>
				<figcaption class="content-img-subtitle">
                    Store your quilts safely.
						<span class="credit">Marcie Cheatham / E+ / Getty Images</span>
				</figcaption>
		</figure>
				<div class="expert-content-text">
					<h3 class="item-heading">
						
							1.&nbsp;
Learn About Fabric
					</h3>
	
							<p>Fabrics are the backbone of our quilts, but you might be surprised how many people begin to assemble their first quilt without putting fabric characteristics to work for them. It&#39;s much easier to make a quilt once you understand how to care for your fabrics and why <a data-inlink="qY1KYNMxQqVTd5GErm1KBQ&#61;&#61;" href="/od/quiltblockconstruction/ss/patchwork_block_5.htm" data-component="link" data-source="inlineLink" data-type="internalLink" data-ordinal="1">quilting patches are cut using specific guidelines.</a> Two important must-knows are:</p><ul><li><a href="/od/fabricembellishment/ss/fabric_grain.htm" data-component="link" data-source="inlineLink" data-type="internalLink" data-ordinal="2">How Understanding Fabric Grain Can Improve Your Quiltmaking Skills</a></li><li><a href="/od/fabricembellishment/a/prewash_fabric.htm" data-component="link" data-source="inlineLink" data-type="internalLink" data-ordinal="3">Prewashing Pros and Cons</a></li></ul>
				</div>
			</section>

<div id="adsense1" adsense-numlinks="2" adsense-displaylabel="true" class="adsense-slot adsense"></div>
		

		<section class="list-unit group">
		<figure class="content-img content-img-small right-gutter">
			<div class="content-img-wrapper">
<img src="http://f.tqn.com/y/quilting/1/0/C/-/-/-/sewing_seams_ss_2_blog.jpg" alt="How to Sew a 1/4 Inch Seam - &copy; Janet Wickell" width="170" height="123" class="" data-pinit-img-url="http://f.tqn.com/y/quilting/1/S/C/-/-/-/sewing_seams_ss_2_blog.jpg" data-description="10 Things Every Quilter Should Know About Quilting: Sew a Quarter Inch Seam Allowance" itemprop="image" >
			
<a href="http://pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=http://quilting.about.com/od/quiltpatternsprojects/tp/quilting_skills.htm?utm_source=pinterest&amp;utm_medium=social&amp;utm_campaign=shareurlbuttons_nip&media=http://f.tqn.com/y/quilting/1/0/C/-/-/-/sewing_seams_ss_2_blog.jpg&description=10 Things Every Quilter Should Know About Quilting: Sew a Quarter Inch Seam Allowance" data-component="contentListPage" data-source="pinitBtn" data-type="sharePinterest" data-ordinal="2" data-network="pinterest" title="Pin to Pinterest" class="pinit-btn" data-pin-do="skipLink"></a>			</div>
				<figcaption class="content-img-subtitle">
                    Sew a 1/4 Inch Seam.
						<span class="credit">&copy; Janet Wickell</span>
				</figcaption>
		</figure>
				<div class="expert-content-text">
					<h3 class="item-heading">
						
							2.&nbsp;
Sew a Quarter Inch Seam Allowance
					</h3>
	
							<p>Beginning quilters, especially people who are accustomed to sewing garments with 5/8&#34; seam allowances, sometimes have a hard time visualizing and sewing the 1/4&#34; seam allowance used to make quilts. There are tricks to help you get the seam just right -- but you do need to <a href="/od/machinepiecingyourquilts/ss/seam_allowance.htm" data-component="link" data-source="inlineLink" data-type="internalLink" data-ordinal="1">do a few tests before you start sewing</a> patches for a quilt.
							</p>
				</div>
			</section>

		

		<section class="list-unit group">
		<figure class="content-img content-img-small right-gutter">
			<div class="content-img-wrapper">
<img src="http://f.tqn.com/y/quilting/1/0/0/5/-/-/rotary_cutters_170.jpg" alt="Learn How to Rotary Cut Fabric - &copy; Janet Wickell" width="170" height="136" class="" data-pinit-img-url="http://f.tqn.com/y/quilting/1/S/0/5/-/-/rotary_cutters_170.jpg" data-description="10 Things Every Quilter Should Know About Quilting: Develop Rotary Cutting Skills" itemprop="image" >
			
<a href="http://pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=http://quilting.about.com/od/quiltpatternsprojects/tp/quilting_skills.htm?utm_source=pinterest&amp;utm_medium=social&amp;utm_campaign=shareurlbuttons_nip&media=http://f.tqn.com/y/quilting/1/0/0/5/-/-/rotary_cutters_170.jpg&description=10 Things Every Quilter Should Know About Quilting: Develop Rotary Cutting Skills" data-component="contentListPage" data-source="pinitBtn" data-type="sharePinterest" data-ordinal="3" data-network="pinterest" title="Pin to Pinterest" class="pinit-btn" data-pin-do="skipLink"></a>			</div>
				<figcaption class="content-img-subtitle">
                    Learn How to Rotary Cut Fabric.
						<span class="credit">&copy; Janet Wickell</span>
				</figcaption>
		</figure>
				<div class="expert-content-text">
					<h3 class="item-heading">
						
							3.&nbsp;
Develop Rotary Cutting Skills
					</h3>
	
							<p>Rotary cutting is a technique that every new quilter should master, because it allows us to bypass the time-intense method of constructing templates to mark and cut individual pieces of fabric. You&#39;ll love the freedom that rotary tools provide, and speedy cutting is fantastic motivation for continued success.</p><ul><li><a href="/od/rotarycuttingskills/ss/rotary_tools.htm" data-component="link" data-source="inlineLink" data-type="internalLink" data-ordinal="1">Rotary Cutting Tools You&#39;ll Need</a></li><li><a href="/od/rotarycuttingskills/bb/rotary_cutter.htm" data-component="link" data-source="inlineLink" data-type="internalLink" data-ordinal="2">Choose the Best Rotary Cutter</a></li><li><a href="/od/rotarycuttingskills/tp/rotary_safety.htm" data-component="link" data-source="inlineLink" data-type="internalLink" data-ordinal="3">Rotary Cutting Safety</a></li><li><a href="/od/rotarycuttingskills/ss/cutting_strips.htm" data-component="link" data-source="inlineLink" data-type="internalLink" data-ordinal="4">Learn to Cut Long Strips of Quilting Fabric</a></li><li><a href="/od/rotarycuttingskills/ss/cutting_shapes.htm" data-component="link" data-source="inlineLink" data-type="internalLink" data-ordinal="5">Learn How to Cut Patchwork Shapes</a></li></ul>
				</div>
			</section>

<div id="adsense2" adsense-numlinks="2" adsense-displaylabel="true" class="adsense-slot adsense"></div>
		

		<section class="list-unit group">
		<figure class="content-img content-img-small right-gutter">
			<div class="content-img-wrapper">
<img src="http://f.tqn.com/y/quilting/1/L/k/-/0/-/second-set-geese-mystery.jpg" alt=" - " width="300" height="252" class="" data-pinit-img-url="http://f.tqn.com/y/quilting/1/S/k/-/0/-/second-set-geese-mystery.jpg" data-description="10 Things Every Quilter Should Know About Quilting: Learn Strip &amp;amp; Quick Piecing Techniques" itemprop="image" >
			
<a href="http://pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=http://quilting.about.com/od/quiltpatternsprojects/tp/quilting_skills.htm?utm_source=pinterest&amp;utm_medium=social&amp;utm_campaign=shareurlbuttons_nip&media=http://f.tqn.com/y/quilting/1/S/k/-/0/-/second-set-geese-mystery.jpg&description=10 Things Every Quilter Should Know About Quilting: Learn Strip &amp;amp; Quick Piecing Techniques" data-component="contentListPage" data-source="pinitBtn" data-type="sharePinterest" data-ordinal="4" data-network="pinterest" title="Pin to Pinterest" class="pinit-btn" data-pin-do="skipLink"></a>			</div>
		</figure>
				<div class="expert-content-text">
					<h3 class="item-heading">
						
							4.&nbsp;
Learn Strip &amp; Quick Piecing Techniques
					</h3>
	
							<p><a href="/od/quiltingglossaryg/g/strip_piecing.htm" data-inlink="hzrjUqagTa5wC3Vnpl3S6w&#61;&#61;" data-component="link" data-source="inlineLink" data-type="internalLink" data-ordinal="1">Strip piecing</a> and other quick piecing techniques let you sew large chunks of fabric together, then slice off sections to create pre-sewn units. It is <em>so</em> easy! Learn the basics and you&#39;ll be able to create a quick pieced version of just about any quilt block you see. A few most-used techniques include:</p><ul><li><a href="/od/quickpiecingtechniques/ss/halfsquaretria.htm" data-component="link" data-source="inlineLink" data-type="internalLink" data-ordinal="2">Quick Pieced Half Square Triangle Units</a></li><li><a href="/od/quickpiecingtechniques/ss/quarter_squares.htm" data-component="link" data-source="inlineLink" data-type="internalLink" data-ordinal="3">Quick Pieced Quarter Square Triangle Units</a></li><li><a href="/od/quiltpatternsprojects/ss/No-Waste-Flying-Geese-Quilt-Pattern.htm" data-component="link" data-source="inlineLink" data-type="internalLink" data-ordinal="4">No-Waste Flying Geese</a></li></ul><p>Most of my quilt patterns include strip piecing instructions, with illustrations to walk you through each project.
							</p>
				</div>
			</section>

		

		<section class="list-unit group">
		<figure class="content-img content-img-small right-gutter">
			<div class="content-img-wrapper">
<img src="http://f.tqn.com/y/quilting/1/0/a/1/-/-/blog_pressing_back.jpg" alt="How to Press Quilt Blocks - &copy; Janet Wickell" width="170" height="166" class="" data-pinit-img-url="http://f.tqn.com/y/quilting/1/S/a/1/-/-/blog_pressing_back.jpg" data-description="10 Things Every Quilter Should Know About Quilting: Get Pressing Basics Down Pat" itemprop="image" >
			
<a href="http://pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=http://quilting.about.com/od/quiltpatternsprojects/tp/quilting_skills.htm?utm_source=pinterest&amp;utm_medium=social&amp;utm_campaign=shareurlbuttons_nip&media=http://f.tqn.com/y/quilting/1/0/a/1/-/-/blog_pressing_back.jpg&description=10 Things Every Quilter Should Know About Quilting: Get Pressing Basics Down Pat" data-component="contentListPage" data-source="pinitBtn" data-type="sharePinterest" data-ordinal="5" data-network="pinterest" title="Pin to Pinterest" class="pinit-btn" data-pin-do="skipLink"></a>			</div>
				<figcaption class="content-img-subtitle">
                    How to Press Quilt Blocks.
						<span class="credit">&copy; Janet Wickell</span>
				</figcaption>
		</figure>
				<div class="expert-content-text">
					<h3 class="item-heading">
						
							5.&nbsp;
Get Pressing Basics Down Pat
					</h3>
	
							<p>Your piecing accuracy will improve immediately when you take a bit of time to <a href="/od/pressingtechniques/ss/press_blocks.htm" data-component="link" data-source="inlineLink" data-type="internalLink" data-ordinal="1">press your quilt blocks</a> as you make them. You might think extra pressing will slow you down, but you&#39;ll find that you actually <em>save time</em> when your quilt blocks fit together just like they should, without grabbing the dreaded seam ripper.
							</p>
				</div>
			</section>

<div id="adsense3" adsense-numlinks="1" adsense-displaylabel="true" class="adsense-slot adsense"></div>
		

		<section class="list-unit group">
		<figure class="content-img content-img-small right-gutter">
			<div class="content-img-wrapper">
<img src="http://f.tqn.com/y/quilting/1/L/w/u/-/-/nine-to-trace.jpg" alt=" - &copy; Janet Wickell" width="300" height="299" class="" data-pinit-img-url="http://f.tqn.com/y/quilting/1/S/w/u/-/-/nine-to-trace.jpg" data-description="10 Things Every Quilter Should Know About Quilting: Don&#39;t Pitch Those Quilt Blocks Just Yet" itemprop="image" >
			
<a href="http://pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=http://quilting.about.com/od/quiltpatternsprojects/tp/quilting_skills.htm?utm_source=pinterest&amp;utm_medium=social&amp;utm_campaign=shareurlbuttons_nip&media=http://f.tqn.com/y/quilting/1/0/w/u/-/-/nine-to-trace.jpg&description=10 Things Every Quilter Should Know About Quilting: Don't Pitch Those Quilt Blocks Just Yet" data-component="contentListPage" data-source="pinitBtn" data-type="sharePinterest" data-ordinal="6" data-network="pinterest" title="Pin to Pinterest" class="pinit-btn" data-pin-do="skipLink"></a>			</div>
				<figcaption class="content-img-subtitle">
						<span class="credit pull-right">&copy; Janet Wickell</span>
				</figcaption>
		</figure>
				<div class="expert-content-text">
					<h3 class="item-heading">
						
							6.&nbsp;
Don't Pitch Those Quilt Blocks Just Yet
					</h3>
	
							<p>We&#39;ve all sewn quilt blocks that aren&#39;t quite accurate. Most often, they&#39;re smaller than they should be, perhaps because we&#39;ve either sewn a slightly large quarter inch seam allowance or haven&#39;t pressed adequately. Don&#39;t feel discouraged if that happens to you, because a high percentage of &#39;off&#39; quilt blocks can be rescued.</p><p><a href="/od/quiltingcommunity/a/swap_blocks.htm" data-component="link" data-source="inlineLink" data-type="internalLink" data-ordinal="1">How to Fix Quilt Blocks</a>
							</p>
				</div>
			</section>

		

		<section class="list-unit group">
		<figure class="content-img content-img-small right-gutter">
			<div class="content-img-wrapper">
<img src="http://f.tqn.com/y/quilting/1/L/k/8/-/-/mystery_border.jpg" alt="Learn to Sew Quilt Borders - &copy; Janet Wickell" width="300" height="177" class="" data-pinit-img-url="http://f.tqn.com/y/quilting/1/S/k/8/-/-/mystery_border.jpg" data-description="10 Things Every Quilter Should Know About Quilting: Measure and Sew Borders... the Correct Way" itemprop="image" >
			
<a href="http://pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=http://quilting.about.com/od/quiltpatternsprojects/tp/quilting_skills.htm?utm_source=pinterest&amp;utm_medium=social&amp;utm_campaign=shareurlbuttons_nip&media=http://f.tqn.com/y/quilting/1/0/k/8/-/-/mystery_border.jpg&description=10 Things Every Quilter Should Know About Quilting: Measure and Sew Borders... the Correct Way" data-component="contentListPage" data-source="pinitBtn" data-type="sharePinterest" data-ordinal="7" data-network="pinterest" title="Pin to Pinterest" class="pinit-btn" data-pin-do="skipLink"></a>			</div>
				<figcaption class="content-img-subtitle">
                    Learn to Sew Quilt Borders.
						<span class="credit">&copy; Janet Wickell</span>
				</figcaption>
		</figure>
				<div class="expert-content-text">
					<h3 class="item-heading">
						
							7.&nbsp;
Measure and Sew Borders... the Correct Way
					</h3>
	
							<p>Adding one or more borders to the edges of a quilt does more than provide an attractive frame for your work... the process offers an excellent opportunity to square up slightly skewed edges. It isn&#39;t unusual to see beginning quilters determine border length by measuring along the outside edges of a quilt. If the quilt is skewed, that technique ensures it will <em>remain skewed</em>. Learn how to measure and sew butted borders that will improve the structure of a quilt.</p><p><a href="/od/straightsewnborders/ss/straightborders.htm" data-component="link" data-source="inlineLink" data-type="internalLink" data-ordinal="1">How to Measure and Sew Straight Borders</a>
							</p>
				</div>
			</section>

		

		<section class="list-unit group">
		<figure class="content-img content-img-small right-gutter">
			<div class="content-img-wrapper">
<img src="http://f.tqn.com/y/quilting/1/L/E/0/-/-/binding_collage_lg.jpg" alt="How to Sew Mitered Quilt Binding - &copy; Janet Wickell" width="300" height="371" class="" data-pinit-img-url="http://f.tqn.com/y/quilting/1/S/E/0/-/-/binding_collage_lg.jpg" data-description="10 Things Every Quilter Should Know About Quilting: Be Sure to Try Mitered Binding" itemprop="image" >
			
<a href="http://pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=http://quilting.about.com/od/quiltpatternsprojects/tp/quilting_skills.htm?utm_source=pinterest&amp;utm_medium=social&amp;utm_campaign=shareurlbuttons_nip&media=http://f.tqn.com/y/quilting/1/0/E/0/-/-/binding_collage_lg.jpg&description=10 Things Every Quilter Should Know About Quilting: Be Sure to Try Mitered Binding" data-component="contentListPage" data-source="pinitBtn" data-type="sharePinterest" data-ordinal="8" data-network="pinterest" title="Pin to Pinterest" class="pinit-btn" data-pin-do="skipLink"></a>			</div>
				<figcaption class="content-img-subtitle">
                    How to Sew Mitered Quilt Binding.
						<span class="credit">&copy; Janet Wickell</span>
				</figcaption>
		</figure>
				<div class="expert-content-text">
					<h3 class="item-heading">
						
							8.&nbsp;
Be Sure to Try Mitered Binding
					</h3>
	
							<p>Sewing mitered binding to the edges of a quilt has developed a bit of a reputation of being difficult, but is actually a very easy technique. An important step is omitted from nearly all mitered binding instructions, and it creates problems for anyone who&#39;d like to apply binding that&#39;s wider or more narrow than 1/4&#34;. My quilt binding instructions explain.</p><p><a href="/od/bindingaquilt/ss/mitered_binding.htm" data-component="link" data-source="inlineLink" data-type="internalLink" data-ordinal="1">Easy Mitered Quilt Binding</a>
							</p>
				</div>
			</section>

		

		<section class="list-unit group">
		<figure class="content-img content-img-small right-gutter">
			<div class="content-img-wrapper">
<img src="http://f.tqn.com/y/quilting/1/0/B/A/-/-/anniversary_blog.jpg" alt=" - " width="171" height="171" class="" data-pinit-img-url="http://f.tqn.com/y/quilting/1/S/B/A/-/-/anniversary_blog.jpg" data-description="10 Things Every Quilter Should Know About Quilting: Become Familiar with Quilting Terminology" itemprop="image" >
			
<a href="http://pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=http://quilting.about.com/od/quiltpatternsprojects/tp/quilting_skills.htm?utm_source=pinterest&amp;utm_medium=social&amp;utm_campaign=shareurlbuttons_nip&media=http://f.tqn.com/y/quilting/1/0/B/A/-/-/anniversary_blog.jpg&description=10 Things Every Quilter Should Know About Quilting: Become Familiar with Quilting Terminology" data-component="contentListPage" data-source="pinitBtn" data-type="sharePinterest" data-ordinal="9" data-network="pinterest" title="Pin to Pinterest" class="pinit-btn" data-pin-do="skipLink"></a>			</div>
		</figure>
				<div class="expert-content-text">
					<h3 class="item-heading">
						
							9.&nbsp;
Become Familiar with Quilting Terminology
					</h3>
	
							<p>Keep a <a href="/od/quiltingglossary/" data-component="link" data-source="inlineLink" data-type="internalLink" data-ordinal="1">quiltmaking glossary</a> or a basic quilting book at your fingertips when you&#39;re making a quilt or reading quilting articles. When you encounter a term you don&#39;t understand, look it up. It won&#39;t be long before you&#39;re familiar with all the terms you need to know in order to follow quiltmaking instructions.</p><p>Be sure to read <a href="/od/stepbystepquilting/a/make_a_quilt.htm" data-component="link" data-source="inlineLink" data-type="internalLink" data-ordinal="2">How to Make a Quilt</a> -- it includes important information about the skills needed for successful projects.</p><p>Remember that you can search this Web site for any term. The search box changes in appearance sometimes, but is typically in the upper right area of the page. Be sure to add the word &#39;quilting&#39; when you search.
							</p>
				</div>
			</section>

		

		<section class="list-unit group">
		<figure class="content-img content-img-small right-gutter">
			<div class="content-img-wrapper">
<img src="http://f.tqn.com/y/quilting/1/0/L/7/-/-/ugly_quilt_blog.jpg" alt="Little Ugly Quilt - &copy; Janet Wickell" width="170" height="168" class="" data-pinit-img-url="http://f.tqn.com/y/quilting/1/S/L/7/-/-/ugly_quilt_blog.jpg" data-description="10 Things Every Quilter Should Know About Quilting: Don&#39;t Obsess Over Errors" itemprop="image" >
			
<a href="http://pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=http://quilting.about.com/od/quiltpatternsprojects/tp/quilting_skills.htm?utm_source=pinterest&amp;utm_medium=social&amp;utm_campaign=shareurlbuttons_nip&media=http://f.tqn.com/y/quilting/1/0/L/7/-/-/ugly_quilt_blog.jpg&description=10 Things Every Quilter Should Know About Quilting: Don't Obsess Over Errors" data-component="contentListPage" data-source="pinitBtn" data-type="sharePinterest" data-ordinal="10" data-network="pinterest" title="Pin to Pinterest" class="pinit-btn" data-pin-do="skipLink"></a>			</div>
				<figcaption class="content-img-subtitle">
                    Little Ugly Quilt.
						<span class="credit">&copy; Janet Wickell</span>
				</figcaption>
		</figure>
				<div class="expert-content-text">
					<h3 class="item-heading">
						
							10.&nbsp;
Don't Obsess Over Errors
					</h3>
	
							<p>See the little quilt to the left? I like to call it <em>What Was I Thinking?</em> It&#39;s awful, in part because of a (really) busy print at the center of Snowball blocks (which aren&#39;t even recognizable as Snowballs). Using a different fabric in those areas might have resulted in a (somewhat) better quilt, and altering contrast throughout would have been one more plus.</p><p>Understanding <a href="/od/colorfabrics/ss/color_value.htm" data-component="link" data-source="inlineLink" data-type="internalLink" data-ordinal="1">color value</a> is just as important as an understanding of the <a href="/od/colorfabrics/ss/color_quilts.htm" data-component="link" data-source="inlineLink" data-type="internalLink" data-ordinal="2">color wheel</a>, maybe even more so, but it&#39;s essential to learn as much as you can about each of those elements.</p><p>We all make errors, both technical and in our choice of fabrics, but our boo-boos nearly always lead to a better understanding of the quilting process. &#39;Mistakes&#39; are really just learning experiences, analyze them and tuck that knowledge away for the next project. Your skills will grow with every new quilt you sew.
							</p>
				</div>
			</section>

		
	



</article>


